Why do I coded name this project "Xidoo"?

Because was the name of my hometown before the Spaniard
ocupation in Mexico. A kind of tribute to my people.

So, with this in mind clear, the source files are under the folder

├── src
│   ├── add_sub_n.sv
│   ├── comparator.sv
│   ├── fsm_control.sv
│   ├── incrementerN.sv
│   ├── muxN_2_1.sv
│   ├── muxN_4_1.sv
│   ├── regN_en_D.sv
│   ├── single_clk_ram.sv
│   ├── tst_xidoo.sv
│   ├── xidoo_datapath.sv
│   └── xidoo.sv

The top level unit is contained in the file:
    xidoo.sv

This project was compiled using
    ModelSim ALTERA STARTER EDITION 10.3d, Fedora 21 x64

And synthesized in
    Quartus II 64-Bit Wen Edition, Fedora 21 x64

The RTL architectute, schematics are found at
├── docs
│   ├── fsm-in.pdf
│   ├── fsm-out.pdf
│   ├── top-down-design.pdf
│   └── xidoo-datapath.pdf

An examples of waveforms gotten were saved in the folder

├── figures
│   └── fig-1-gcd.bmp
